Good hint!

Here's an analisys of what to build:

Note:When rich text is added to the cell, and existing text is in the cell,copy the value and all font-style properties to a rich text run!

PHPExcel_RichText {	Array of PHPExcel_RichText_ITextElement	addText() --> return PHPExcel_RichText_TextElement	addRichText() --> return PHPExcel_RichText_RichTextRun	addRichTextFromMarkup() --> return PHPExcel_RichText_RichTextRun, fill with <b>...</b>}

PHPExcel_RichText_ITextElement {	getText()	setText()	getFont()}

PHPExcel_RichText_TextElement implements PHPExcel_RichText_ITextElement {	getText()	setText()	getFont() --> null}

PHPExcel_RichText_RichTextRun implements PHPExcel_RichText_ITextElement {	getText()	setText()	getFont() --> PHPExcel_Style_Font

	// Perhaps a special constructor method can be created	// providing the ability to convert from simple markup	// like <b><font name=Ã„rial"><color="000000FF">Hello world!</color></fonr></b>	// (it should not be allowed to repeat elements!)}

PHPExcel_RichText_RichTextRun_Properties {	getBold()	setBold()	getCharset() --> Page 2054 OpenXML reference part 4	setCharset()	getFamily() --> Page 2112 OpenXML reference part 4	setFamily()	getItalic()	setItalic()	getOutline()	setOutline()	getFont() --> Page 2058 OpenXML reference part 4	setFont()	getShadow()	setShadow()	getStrike()	setStrike()	getSize() --> in points	setSize()	getUnderline()	setUnderline()	getVerticalAlignment() --> Page 2064 OpenXML reference part 4	setVerticalAlignment()	getColor()	setColor()}
